  "business_context": "Contract records hold the legal-relationship layer of CRM data. Each contract has parties (the org and one or more counterparties), an effective date, a term length, an end date, a renewal disposition (auto-renewal vs manual), and signed signature artifacts. Contracts drive several distinct workflows: pre-signature (negotiation, redlining, approval routing); signature (e-sign integration with DocuSign, Adobe Sign, HelloSign); active-contract management (renewal-reminder cadence, anniversary milestones); and expiration / termination (renewal opportunities, churn signals). Modeling varies: Salesforce has Contract as a standard object that links to Account with ContractStatus, StartDate, ContractTerm (months), EndDate, ActivatedDate, OwnerExpirationNotice. HubSpot added Contracts as an Enterprise feature. EspoCRM has Contract in the Sales Pack module. Attio doesn't have a standard Contract entity. CiviCRM and Bloomerang don't have it natively — nonprofits typically use Documents for signed grant agreements and pledges. Contracts often have line items (specific services / products being contracted) similar to Quote line items. When interviewing clients, surface \"Contract\" by asking whether they need to track signed agreements with structured terms (effective dates, renewal logic, parties) separately from generic document attachments.",
  "catalog_id": "contract",
